Because AWS account setup was not available, you used serverless-offline for local practice.
Install the local plugin:
npm init -y
npm install serverless-offline
Then update serverless.yml by adding the plugins section.
4.1 serverless.yml after adding serverless-offline
org: visioncytechlab
service: serverless1http

provider:
  name: aws
  runtime: python3.12

functions:
  hello:
    handler: handler.hello
    events:
      - httpApi:
          path: /
          method: get

plugins:
  - serverless-offline
Start the local server:
serverless offline
Open in browser:
http://localhost:3000
Note: At this stage, the local GET endpoint returned a basic response such as Hello from Serverless or GET working.
